# Route Registration Checklist

Every new route in this app requires updates in **all four places**. Missing any one causes a broken header title, missing nav link, or invisible page.

## The Four Places

| File | What to add |
|------|-------------|
| `App.tsx` | `<Route path="..." element={...} />` inside the Layout |
| `Layout.tsx` `routeConfig` | `'/path': { title: 'Page Title', icon: IconComponent }` |
| `Sidebar.tsx` `navigationItems` | `{ name: '...', href: '/path', icon: IconComponent }` |
| `BottomTabBar.tsx` or `More.tsx` | Tab entry or `<MenuRow>` link for mobile nav |

## Example

Adding a new `/goals` page:

```tsx
// App.tsx
const Goals = lazy(() => import('./pages/Goals').then(m => ({ default: m.Goals })));
<Route path="goals" element={<Suspense fallback={null}><Goals /></Suspense>} />

// Layout.tsx routeConfig
'/goals': { title: 'Goals', icon: Target },

// Sidebar.tsx navigationItems
{ name: 'Goals', href: '/goals', icon: Target }

// More.tsx (mobile) or BottomTabBar.tsx
<MenuRow href="/goals" icon={Target} label="Goals" />
```

## Rule

When adding or renaming a route, always update all four locations before finishing. The `routeConfig` in `Layout.tsx` drives the page header — if it's missing, the header silently falls back to "Dashboard".
